remarks: If inhabited sets of natural numbers always have minimal elements, excluded middle follows.  The argument is essentially the same as ~ regexmid and the larger lesson is that although natural numbers may behave "non-constructively" even in a constructive set theory (for example see ~ nndceq or ~ nntri3or ), sets of natural numbers are a different animal.  (Contributed by Jim Kingdon, 6-Sep-2019.)
